Description: extensions to the C++ standard library Abseil is an open-source collection of C++ library code designed to augment the C++ standard library. The Abseil library code is collected from Google's C++ codebase and has been extensively tested and used in production. In some cases, Abseil provides pieces missing from the C++ standard; in others, Abseil provides alternatives to the standard for special needs.
Package-List: libabsl-dev deb libdevel optional arch=any libabsl20240722 deb libs optional arch=any
Testsuite-Triggers: cmake, g++, libgmock-dev, libgtest-dev, make, pkg-config
